%jdbc(hive)
drop table if exists mortinie.sbb_travel_delay;
create table mortinie.sbb_travel_delay
stored as parquet
as
with q as (
    select
        TripID as trip_id,
        LineID as line_id,
        StopName as stopname,
        TransportType as transport_type,
        from_utc_timestamp(from_unixtime(cast(unix_timestamp(TripDate, 'dd.MM.yyyy') as bigint)), 'UTC') as trip_date,
        from_unixtime(unix_timestamp(TripDate, 'dd.MM.yyyy'), 'u') as trip_day,
        from_utc_timestamp(from_unixtime(cast(unix_timestamp(ArrivalTime, 'dd.MM.yyyy HH:mm') as bigint)), 'UTC') as arrival_time,
        from_utc_timestamp(from_unixtime(cast(unix_timestamp(ActualArrivalTime, 'dd.MM.yyyy HH:mm:ss') as bigint)), 'UTC') as actual_arrival_time
    from mortinie.sbb
    where ArrivalTimeStatus = 'GESCHAETZT' and ActualArrivalTime is not null and ArrivalTime is not null and ActualArrivalTime != '' and ArrivalTime != ''
)
select
    trip_id,
    line_id,
    trip_date,
    trip_day,
    stopname,
    transport_type,
    arrival_time,
    actual_arrival_time,
    unix_timestamp(actual_arrival_time) - unix_timestamp(arrival_time) as delay,
    case
    when unix_timestamp(actual_arrival_time) - unix_timestamp(arrival_time) < 0 then 0
    else unix_timestamp(actual_arrival_time) - unix_timestamp(arrival_time) 
    end as positive_delay
from q;

with q as (
    select hour(arrival_time) as arrival_hour, stopname, positive_delay, trip_day
    from mortinie.sbb_travel_delay
)
select trip_day, avg(positive_delay) as avg_delay, std(positive_delay) as std_delay
from q
group by trip_day;
